Vice President Joe Biden has announced that Bruce Reed is stepping down as his Chief of Staff and will be replaced by senior aide Steve Ricchetti. Reed will become President of The Eli and Edythe Broad Foundation. Shailagh J. Murray will become the Deputy Chief of Staff while continuing in her role as Communications Director. Ricchetti has a 30-year career in public service, business, and political life, including positions on Capitol Hill and the Clinton Administration. Murray has worked as a journalist for 20 years. Reed has been with the Vice President's staff since January 2011 and has led the team through budget negotiations, the re-election campaign, and efforts to tighten gun laws. Ricchetti's formal title will be Assistant to the President and Chief of Staff to the Vice President, while Murray's formal title will be Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy Chief of Staff to the Vice President.